  "prompt": "What is the proof for triangular law of vectors?",
  "response": "The triangular law of vector addition states that if two vectors \\(\\mathbf{A}\\) and \\(\\mathbf{B}\\) are represented as two sides of a triangle taken in sequence, then the resultant vector \\(\\mathbf{R} = \\mathbf{A} + \\mathbf{B}\\) is represented by the third side of the triangle taken in the opposite direction.\n\n### Proof:\n\n1. **Vector Representation**: Consider two vectors \\(\\mathbf{A}\\) and \\(\\mathbf{B}\\). Place the tail of vector \\(\\mathbf{B}\\) at the head of vector \\(\\mathbf{A}\\). This is equivalent to arranging the two vectors such that they form two sides of a triangle with vector \\(\\mathbf{R}\\) as the third side.\n\n2. **Construction of Triangle**: \n   - Start at a point \\(O\\). Let this be the tail of vector \\(\\mathbf{A}\\).\n   - From point \\(O\\), draw vector \\(\\mathbf{A}\\) to point \\(P\\).\n   - From point \\(P\\), draw vector \\(\\mathbf{B}\\) to point \\(Q\\).\n\n3. **Resultant Vector**: The vector \\(\\mathbf{R}\\), which is the sum of \\(\\mathbf{A}\\) and \\(\\mathbf{B}\\), is directed from the start point \\(O\\) to the end point \\(Q\\).\n\n4. **Mathematical Confirmation**: \n   - Using vector addition, \\(\\mathbf{R} = \\mathbf{A} + \\mathbf{B}\\).\n   - This means if you travel along \\(\\mathbf{A}\\) and then along \\(\\mathbf{B}\\), it's equivalent to traveling directly along \\(\\mathbf{R}\\).\n\n5. **Graphical Representation**: In the triangle \\(OPQ\\):\n   - The side \\(OQ\\) represents \\(\\mathbf{R}\\).\n   - \\(OP\\) represents \\(\\mathbf{A}\\).\n   - \\(PQ\\) represents \\(\\mathbf{B}\\).\n\nSince the vectors \\(\\mathbf{A}\\) and \\(\\mathbf{B}\\) completely define the path from point \\(O\\) to point \\(Q\\), the third side, \\(\\mathbf{R}\\) (from \\(O\\) to \\(Q\\)), completes the triangle, proving the triangular law of vector addition. This illustrates that adding two vectors as per the triangular law results in a vector represented by the triangle's third side taken in reverse order.",
